# Microservice

The microservice is a small H3/Nitro server intended for operational tasks (e.g., DB encryption key rotation migration) and background helpers.

## Structure

- Entry: microservice/server.ts; logs at microservice/server/logger.ts
- Routes: microservice/routes/migrate.get.ts, migrate.post.ts, test.get.ts
- Clients: microservice/clients/prismaClient.ts, redisClient.ts
- Prisma: microservice/prisma/schema.prisma and migrations; generated reencrypt/*
- Utilities: microservice/lib/bull.ts for BullMQ setup
- Docker: microservice/Dockerfile supports a special runner-keyrotate target used by staging CronJob

## Usage in deployment

- Exposed as a ClusterIP Service on port 3050; main app talks to it via MICROSERVICE_INTERNAL_URL
- The staging CronJob uses the runner-keyrotate image to:
  - Patch secret ${SECRET_DB}
  - Roll deployments
  - Hit /migrate endpoint to run reencrypt migration over the DB with updated key set

## Notes

- The microservice schema is a subset of the main app’s and may lag on some entities not needed for rotation tasks. When adding encrypted models in the app that affect rotation flows, mirror them here and regenerate prisma client and reencrypt code
